  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The investigators leading hypotheses are:

        -  Oral therapy with montelukast may lead to improved sleep study findings in children with
           mild to moderate Obstructive Sleep Apnea Syndrome (OSAS) who require surgical removal of
           adenoids and tonsils for OSAS.

        -  A significant proportion of the children with OSAS treated with montelukast will show
           reduced severity of OSAS, and this will remove the need for surgical intervention.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
